text: Phillip Leslie Wilcher (born 16 March 1958) is an Australian pianist and classical music composer. He was a founding member of the children's music group The Wiggles. When Wilcher published his first work, "Daybreak", at the age of 14, he was one of the youngest classical composers in Australia. ==References== Category:1958 births Category:Australian composers Category:Australian pianists Category:Living people Category:Musicians from Sydney Category:Writers from Sydney Category:Actors from Sydney
